  "texts": [
    "After passing through this CNN, the dimensions of the features for the two drugs become [batch_size, 160, 85].",
    "In addition, the specific output about the convolution of each layer and the parameters are shown in Table 3 for the data of Conv1, Conv2 and Conv3.",
    "Then, we extract the key features of the sequence information using the Mix Attention module.",
    "MixAttention module consists of drug-pair attention, where both drugs share the same weights.",
    "We find that the best experimental results are achieved when the head hyperparameter is 4 in our experiments, whose specific output size and parameters for the MixAttention Layer are recorded in Table 3.h (l) d = sigmoid   N � j=1 j h (l) j  , = softmax(AX (l) W (l) SAG), (12) Z i = ReLU (Conv1d(X i, W i)).The attention values of different heads of drug A for drug B are computed separately for a given convolutional feature D 1 of drug A and convolutional feature D 2 of drug B."
